JOB POSTING // Detroit Digital/ NTR Coordinator

DATE: July 17, 2017
TITLE: Digital/ NTR Coordinator
LOCATION: Detroit, MI
DESCRIPTION: Beasley Media Group is one of the nation’s leading media companies, with successful properties in thirteen cities extending from Boston to Las Vegas.  While Beasley’s roots are in radio, the company is experiencing exceptional success with its digital properties and local events.  Beasley Media Group – Detroit is looking for a Digital/NTR coordinator to support its continued growth. The disorganized, dispassionate, or disinterested need not apply!  However, if you’re good at the metaphorical spinning of plates: calmly working on several projects simultaneously while communicating with diverse personality types — this job may be for you!
The successful candidate will be a member of the digital team and be responsible for the intake of sales orders with digital or event components, and s/he will ensure that orders are fulfilled as specified — by categorizing, scheduling, assigning, and fulfilling work.  This individual will also create webpages, contests, create email blasts, create and schedule social posts, and create digital and non-traditional revenue (NTR) recaps for Beasley sales.
QUALIFICATIONS: 

A customer-focused person who can work within a diverse fast-paced team environment with exceptional attention to detail
Microsoft Office Suite, WordPress administration and basic Photoshop skills
Excellent written and oral communication skills
Ability to learn new digital platforms with minimal training
Ability to adhere to internal and external due dates and ensure all elements within sales campaigns are running and pacing as expected
Out-of-the-box problem solving ability
Associate’s degree or higher preferred

Last Date for Consideration:  July 26th, 2017
E-mail: [email protected]com.   No Calls Please.
Beasley Media Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.


JOB POSTING // Philadelphia Account Executives – Full Time

DATE: July 11, 2017
TITLE: Account Executives – Full Time
LOCATION: Philadelphia
DESCRIPTION: Beasley Media Group is searching for sales professionals to develop and sell advertising and marketing campaigns to new and existing clients for their local radio stations. Responsibilities include soliciting new business through prospecting and cold calling, managing and growing existing assigned accounts and budgets, as well as identifying client advertising needs. The position includes contacting prospective customers to sell radio time for the broadcasting station/network. The ideal candidate will develop and present customized solutions to meet those clients’ needs. The successful candidate will cultivate and maintain relationships with clients by providing top quality service.
QUALIFICATIONS: 

Must have a passion for sales;
Must prepare promotional plans, sales literature, and advertising proposals;
Must develop proposals utilizing MS office products;
Must investigate and resolve customer problems;
Communicate with other departments to assure quality service in placing orders;
Arrange promotional events;
Attend sales meeting, training sessions, and client remotes;
Must have valid driver’s license with stellar driving record.

Last date for consideration: Until filled
Applicants may email:   [email protected] 
Beasley Media Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.


JOB POSTING // Philadelphia IT Support Engineer

DATE: July 11, 2017
TITLE: IT Support Engineer
LOCATION: Philadelphia
DESCRIPTION: Beasley Media Group Philadelphia – home to Philadelphia’s most listened to radio stations: 93.3 WMMR-FM, 102.9 WMGK-FM, 97.5 The Fanatic, and 95.7 BEN-FM – is looking for an Junior to mid-level IT Support Engineer to join the team in our Information Technology department.  The ideal candidate will be responsible for supporting the IT infrastructure for the Philadelphia market. The candidate will have knowledge of commonly used concepts, practices, and procedures regarding Networking, Microsoft Server, Office, VMware, Cisco and Citrix in production environments.
QUALIFICATIONS: 

Working knowledge of with Cisco / HP Network Routers, Switches, VPN and Firewalls.
Experience working with radio automation software. “Preferred but not required”
Working knowledge of VMware VSphere environment, VEEAM Backup and other backup systems management.
Microsoft Server OS 2008 R2, 2012 R2
IT Project management helpful.
Windows Server infrastructure including Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, WINS, etc.
Microsoft Office 2010-2016, OFFICE 365 and SharePoint Administrator experience.
Microsoft OS Win7PRO to Win10PRO, APPLE OS-X, VMware vSphere ESXi 6.0
Provide helpdesk support to users as required on and off site.
Aptitude to learn new technologies quickly

Last date for consideration: Until filled
 Contact: [email protected]
Beasley Media Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.


JOB POSTING // NAPLES, FL Corporate Human Resources Manager

DATE: July 11, 2017
TITLE: Corporate Human Resources Manager 
LOCATION: Naples, FL
DESCRIPTION:Beasley Media Group, Inc., a subsidiary of Beasley Broadcast Group, Inc. (NASDAQ: BBGI), is committed to delivering the very best entertainment content, results and service for our audiences, advertisers and communities as well as providing a respectful, collaborative and innovative environment for our trusted employees.
We’re looking for a dynamic Human Resources Manager to maintain and enhance the organization’s human resources by planning, implementing, and evaluating employee relations and human resources policies, programs, and practices.
Candidates must be excellent communicators with passion, energy and a willingness to learn and grow. If you are ready to work for an outstanding company that values its people, we’d love to hear from you!
Skills: Hiring, Human Resources Management, Benefits Administration, Performance Management, Communication Processes, Compensation and Wage Structure, Supports Diversity, Classifying Employees, Employment Law, Laws Against Sexual Harassment, Organization
QUALIFICATIONS: 

Maintains the work structure by updating job requirements and job descriptions for all positions.
Maintains organization staff by establishing a recruiting, testing, and interviewing program; counseling managers on candidate selection; conducting and analyzing exit interviews; recommending changes.
Prepares employees for assignments by establishing and conducting orientation and training programs.
Maintains a pay plan by conducting periodic pay surveys; scheduling and conducting job evaluations; preparing pay budgets; monitoring and scheduling individual pay actions; recommending, planning, and implementing pay structure revisions.


Ensures planning, monitoring, and appraisal of employee work results by training managers to coach and discipline employees; scheduling management conferences with employees; hearing and resolving employee grievances; counseling employees and supervisors.
Maintains employee benefits programs and informs employees of benefits by studying and assessing benefit needs and trends; recommending benefit programs to management; directing the processing of benefit claims; obtaining and evaluating benefit contract bids; awarding benefit contracts; designing and conducting educational programs on benefit programs.
Ensures legal compliance by monitoring and implementing applicable human resource federal and state requirements; conducting investigations; maintaining records; representing the organization at hearings.
Maintains management guidelines by preparing, updating, and recommending human resource policies and procedures.
Maintains historical human resource records by designing a filing and retrieval system; keeping past and current records.
Maintains professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies.
Completes human resource operational requirements by scheduling and assigning employees; following up on work results.
Maintains human resource staff by recruiting, selecting, orienting, and training employees.
Maintains human resource staff job results by counseling and disciplining employees; planning, monitoring, and appraising job results.
Contributes to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed.


Last date for consideration: Until filled
Interested applicants may submit resume to [email protected].
Beasley Media Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

About Beasley Media Group:
Beasley Media Group, Inc. is a subsidiary of Beasley Broadcast Group, Inc., which owns and operates 63 stations (45 FM and 18 AM) in 15 large and mid-size markets in the United States. Approximately 19 million consumers listen to Beasley radio stations weekly over-the-air, online, on smartphones and tablets and engage with the Company’s brands and personalities through digital platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, text, apps and email.  For more information, please visit www.bbgi.com.

